{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":809,"text":"Well, the subject of difficult negotiation"},{"time":3198,"text":"reminds me of one of my favorite stories\nfrom the Middle East,"},{"time":7000,"text":"of a man who left\nto his three sons, 17 camels."},{"time":10778,"text":"To the first son, he left half the camels;"},{"time":13000,"text":"to the second son,\nhe left a third of the camels;"},{"time":15414,"text":"and to the youngest son,\nhe left a ninth of the camels."},{"time":18033,"text":"The three sons got into a negotiation --\n17 doesn't divide by two."},{"time":21871,"text":"It doesn't divide by three."},{"time":23633,"text":"It doesn't divide by nine."},{"time":25196,"text":"Brotherly tempers started to get strained."},{"time":27466,"text":"Finally, in desperation,"},{"time":28769,"text":"they went and they consulted\na wise old woman."},{"time":32454,"text":"The wise old woman thought\nabout their problem for a long time,"},{"time":35453,"text":"and finally she came back and said,\n\"Well, I don't know if I can help you,"},{"time":38981,"text":"but at least, if you want,\nyou can have my camel.\""},{"time":41382,"text":"So then, they had 18 camels."},{"time":42874,"text":"The first son took his half --\nhalf of 18 is nine."},{"time":45756,"text":"The second son took his third --\na third of 18 is six."},{"time":48474,"text":"The youngest son took his ninth --\na ninth of 18 is two."},{"time":52370,"text":"You get 17."},{"time":54583,"text":"They had one camel left over."},{"time":56417,"text":"They gave it back to the wise old woman."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58369,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":60000,"text":"Now, if you think\nabout that story for a moment,"},{"time":62263,"text":"I think it resembles a lot\nof the difficult negotiations"},{"time":65858,"text":"we get involved in."},{"time":67096,"text":"They start off like 17 camels,\nno way to resolve it."},{"time":69596,"text":"Somehow, what we need to do"},{"time":71056,"text":"is step back from those situations,\nlike that wise old woman,"},{"time":74761,"text":"look at the situation through fresh eyes"},{"time":76817,"text":"and come up with an 18th camel."},{"time":79873,"text":"Finding that 18th camel\nin the world's conflicts"},{"time":82663,"text":"has been my life passion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84845,"text":"I basically see humanity\na bit like those three brothers."},{"time":88000,"text":"We're all one family."},{"time":90145,"text":"We know that scientifically,"},{"time":92118,"text":"thanks to the communications revolution,"},{"time":94088,"text":"all the tribes on the planet --\nall 15,000 tribes --"},{"time":97680,"text":"are in touch with each other."},{"time":100283,"text":"And it's a big family reunion."},{"time":102700,"text":"And yet, like many family reunions,"},{"time":104406,"text":"it's not all peace and light."},{"time":106653,"text":"There's a lot of conflict,"},{"time":108578,"text":"and the question is:\nHow do we deal with our differences?"},{"time":112000,"text":"How do we deal with\nour deepest differences,"},{"time":114120,"text":"given the human propensity for conflict"},{"time":116853,"text":"and the human genius at devising\nweapons of enormous destruction?"},{"time":121404,"text":"That's the question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123177,"text":"As I've spent the last better part\nof three decades, almost four,"},{"time":128000,"text":"traveling the world,"},{"time":130079,"text":"trying to work, getting\ninvolved in conflicts"},{"time":133472,"text":"ranging from Yugoslavia to the Middle East"},{"time":136876,"text":"to Chechnya to Venezuela --"},{"time":138624,"text":"some of the most difficult conflicts\non the face of the planet --"},{"time":141721,"text":"I've been asking myself that question."},{"time":143836,"text":"And I think I've found, in some ways,\nwhat is the secret to peace."},{"time":147256,"text":"It's actually surprisingly simple."},{"time":150000,"text":"It's not easy, but it's simple."},{"time":153200,"text":"It's not even new."},{"time":154455,"text":"It may be one of our most\nancient human heritages."},{"time":157853,"text":"The secret to peace is us."},{"time":160662,"text":"It's us who act as a surrounding\ncommunity around any conflict,"},{"time":165828,"text":"who can play a constructive role."}]},{"cues":[{"time":168000,"text":"Let me give you just a story, an example."},{"time":171944,"text":"About 20 years ago,"},{"time":173120,"text":"I was in South Africa,\nworking with the parties in that conflict,"},{"time":176385,"text":"and I had an extra month,"},{"time":177672,"text":"so I spent some time living\nwith several groups of San Bushmen."},{"time":182262,"text":"I was curious about them, about the way\nin which they resolve conflict."},{"time":186230,"text":"Because, after all, within living memory,\nthey were hunters and gatherers,"},{"time":190000,"text":"living pretty much\nlike our ancestors lived"},{"time":192380,"text":"for maybe 99 percent of the human story."},{"time":195213,"text":"And all the men have these poison arrows\nthat they use for hunting --"},{"time":198600,"text":"absolutely fatal."},{"time":200142,"text":"So how do they deal\nwith their differences?"},{"time":202460,"text":"Well, what I learned is, whenever\ntempers rise in those communities,"},{"time":207073,"text":"someone goes and hides\nthe poison arrows out in the bush,"},{"time":210668,"text":"and then everyone sits around\nin a circle like this,"},{"time":214327,"text":"and they sit and they talk and they talk."},{"time":217303,"text":"It may take two days,\nthree days, four days,"},{"time":219638,"text":"but they don't rest\nuntil they find a resolution"},{"time":223000,"text":"or better yet -- a reconciliation."},{"time":225000,"text":"And if tempers are still too high,"},{"time":227057,"text":"then they send someone\noff to visit some relatives,"},{"time":229620,"text":"as a cooling-off period."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231398,"text":"Well, that system is, I think,\nprobably the system"},{"time":234407,"text":"that kept us alive to this point,"},{"time":236167,"text":"given our human tendencies."},{"time":238841,"text":"That system, I call \"the third side.\""},{"time":242056,"text":"Because if you think about it,\nnormally when we think of conflict,"},{"time":245199,"text":"when we describe it,"},{"time":246374,"text":"there's always two sides --"},{"time":247771,"text":"it's Arabs versus Israelis,\nlabor versus management,"},{"time":250501,"text":"husband versus wife,\nRepublicans versus Democrats."},{"time":253676,"text":"But what we don't often see"},{"time":255485,"text":"is that there's always a third side,"},{"time":257875,"text":"and the third side of the conflict is us,\nit's the surrounding community,"},{"time":261571,"text":"it's the friends, the allies,"},{"time":263000,"text":"the family members, the neighbors."},{"time":264832,"text":"And we can play\nan incredibly constructive role."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268220,"text":"Perhaps the most fundamental way\nin which the third side can help"},{"time":273059,"text":"is to remind the parties\nof what's really at stake."},{"time":276336,"text":"For the sake of the kids,\nfor the sake of the family,"},{"time":278864,"text":"for the sake of the community,\nfor the sake of the future,"},{"time":281658,"text":"let's stop fighting for a moment\nand start talking."},{"time":284806,"text":"Because, the thing is,"},{"time":286305,"text":"when we're involved in conflict,"},{"time":287902,"text":"it's very easy to lose perspective."},{"time":290485,"text":"It's very easy to react."},{"time":292548,"text":"Human beings -- we're reaction machines."},{"time":295445,"text":"And as the saying goes,"},{"time":296842,"text":"when angry, you will make the best speech"},{"time":299389,"text":"you will ever regret."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300898,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":302580,"text":"And so the third side reminds us of that."},{"time":305600,"text":"The third side helps us go to the balcony,"},{"time":307649,"text":"which is a metaphor\nfor a place of perspective,"},{"time":310379,"text":"where we can keep our eyes on the prize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312809,"text":"Let me tell you a little story\nfrom my own negotiating experience."},{"time":316413,"text":"Some years ago, I was involved\nas a facilitator in some very tough talks"},{"time":321508,"text":"between the leaders of Russia\nand the leaders of Chechnya."},{"time":325429,"text":"There was a war going on, as you know."},{"time":327795,"text":"And we met in the Hague,\nin the Peace Palace,"},{"time":331000,"text":"in the same room where the Yugoslav\nwar-crimes tribunal was taking place."},{"time":336131,"text":"And the talks got off\nto a rather rocky start"},{"time":339027,"text":"when the vice president of Chechnya\nbegan by pointing at the Russians"},{"time":342459,"text":"and said, \"You should stay\nright here in your seats,"},{"time":345000,"text":"because you're going\nto be on trial for war crimes.\""},{"time":347835,"text":"And then he turned to me and said,"},{"time":349669,"text":"\"You're an American."},{"time":350875,"text":"Look at what you Americans\nare doing in Puerto Rico.\""},{"time":354125,"text":"And my mind started racing, \"Puerto Rico?\nWhat do I know about Puerto Rico?\""},{"time":357772,"text":"I started reacting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358948,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":359973,"text":"But then, I tried to remember\nto go to the balcony."},{"time":362833,"text":"And then when he paused"},{"time":364055,"text":"and everyone looked at me for a response,"},{"time":366160,"text":"from a balcony perspective,\nI was able to thank him for his remarks"},{"time":369562,"text":"and say, \"I appreciate\nyour criticism of my country"},{"time":372363,"text":"and I take it as a sign\nthat we're among friends"},{"time":374834,"text":"and can speak candidly to one another.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":376749,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":377774,"text":"\"And what we're here to do is not\nto talk about Puerto Rico or the past."},{"time":381179,"text":"We're here to see\nif we can figure out a way"},{"time":383384,"text":"to stop the suffering\nand the bloodshed in Chechnya.\""},{"time":386851,"text":"The conversation got back on track."},{"time":389190,"text":"That's the role of the third side,"},{"time":390873,"text":"to help the parties go to the balcony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393822,"text":"Now let me take you, for a moment,"},{"time":396073,"text":"to what's widely regarded as the world's\nmost difficult conflict,"},{"time":399162,"text":"or the most impossible conflict,\nthe Middle East."},{"time":401727,"text":"Question is: where's the third side there?"},{"time":405000,"text":"How could we possibly go to the balcony?"},{"time":407505,"text":"Now, I don't pretend to have an answer\nto the Middle East conflict,"},{"time":411506,"text":"but I think I've got a first step --\nliterally, a first step --"},{"time":415490,"text":"something that any one of us\ncould do as third-siders."},{"time":418501,"text":"Let me just ask you one question first."},{"time":420732,"text":"How many of you in the last years"},{"time":424749,"text":"have ever found yourself\nworrying about the Middle East"},{"time":427808,"text":"and wondering what anyone could do?"},{"time":429584,"text":"Just out of curiosity, how many of you?"},{"time":431725,"text":"OK, so the great majority of us."},{"time":434717,"text":"And here, it's so far away."},{"time":436345,"text":"Why do we pay so much attention\nto this conflict?"},{"time":439285,"text":"Is it the number of deaths?"},{"time":441000,"text":"There are a hundred times more people\nwho die in a conflict in Africa"},{"time":444421,"text":"than in the Middle East."},{"time":445596,"text":"No, it's because of the story,"},{"time":447707,"text":"because we feel personally\ninvolved in that story."},{"time":451439,"text":"Whether we're Christians, Muslims or Jews,\nreligious or non-religious,"},{"time":455292,"text":"we feel we have a personal stake in it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":457189,"text":"Stories matter;"},{"time":458364,"text":"as an anthropologist, I know that."},{"time":460146,"text":"Stories are what we use\nto transmit knowledge."},{"time":463788,"text":"They give meaning to our lives."},{"time":465333,"text":"That's what we tell here\nat TED, we tell stories."},{"time":468054,"text":"Stories are the key."},{"time":469232,"text":"And so my question is --"},{"time":472470,"text":"yes, let's try and resolve the politics\nthere in the Middle East,"},{"time":476670,"text":"but let's also take a look at the story."},{"time":479218,"text":"Let's try to get at the root\nof what it's all about."},{"time":481686,"text":"Let's see if we can apply\nthe third side to it."},{"time":483930,"text":"What would that mean?\nWhat is the story there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":486758,"text":"Now, as anthropologists, we know\nthat every culture has an origin story."},{"time":491496,"text":"What's the origin story\nof the Middle East?"},{"time":493621,"text":"In a phrase, it's:"},{"time":495000,"text":"Four thousand years ago,"},{"time":496615,"text":"a man and his family walked\nacross the Middle East,"},{"time":500629,"text":"and the world has never\nbeen the same since."},{"time":503811,"text":"That man, of course, was Abraham."},{"time":507309,"text":"And what he stood for was unity,\nthe unity of the family;"},{"time":511000,"text":"he's the father of us all."},{"time":513000,"text":"But it's not just what he stood for,\nit's what his message was."},{"time":516013,"text":"His basic message was unity too,"},{"time":518000,"text":"the interconnectedness of it all,\nthe unity of it all."},{"time":521234,"text":"And his basic value was respect,"},{"time":524568,"text":"was kindness toward strangers."},{"time":526460,"text":"That's what he's known for,\nhis hospitality."},{"time":530048,"text":"So in that sense,"},{"time":531699,"text":"he's the symbolic third side\nof the Middle East."},{"time":535683,"text":"He's the one who reminds us\nthat we're all part of a greater whole."},{"time":540447,"text":"Now, think about that for a moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544414,"text":"Today, we face the scourge of terrorism."},{"time":547291,"text":"What is terrorism?"},{"time":549148,"text":"Terrorism is basically\ntaking an innocent stranger"},{"time":552431,"text":"and treating them as an enemy\nwhom you kill in order to create fear."},{"time":557603,"text":"What's the opposite of terrorism?"},{"time":559976,"text":"It's taking an innocent stranger"},{"time":561720,"text":"and treating them as a friend\nwhom you welcome into your home,"},{"time":566131,"text":"in order to sow and create understanding"},{"time":568847,"text":"or respect, or love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":571593,"text":"So what if, then, you took\nthe story of Abraham,"},{"time":576277,"text":"which is a third-side story,"},{"time":577934,"text":"what if that could be --"},{"time":580000,"text":"because Abraham stands for hospitality --"},{"time":583345,"text":"what if that could be\nan antidote to terrorism?"},{"time":586583,"text":"What if that could be a vaccine\nagainst religious intolerance?"},{"time":590429,"text":"How would you bring that story to life?"},{"time":593000,"text":"Now, it's not enough just to tell a story."},{"time":595786,"text":"That's powerful, but people need\nto experience the story."},{"time":599204,"text":"They need to be able to live the story."},{"time":601182,"text":"How would you do that?"},{"time":602482,"text":"And that was my thinking\nof how would you do that."},{"time":605000,"text":"And that's what comes\nto the first step here."},{"time":607167,"text":"Because the simple way to do that is:"},{"time":609914,"text":"you go for a walk."},{"time":611723,"text":"You go for a walk\nin the footsteps of Abraham."},{"time":615162,"text":"You retrace the footsteps of Abraham."},{"time":618114,"text":"Because walking has a real power."},{"time":621410,"text":"You know, as an anthropologist,\nwalking is what made us human."},{"time":624491,"text":"It's funny -- when you walk,\nyou walk side-by-side,"},{"time":628710,"text":"in the same common direction."},{"time":631352,"text":"Now if I were to come to you face-to-face"},{"time":633437,"text":"and come this close to you,"},{"time":635707,"text":"you would feel threatened."},{"time":639717,"text":"But if I walk shoulder-to-shoulder,"},{"time":641796,"text":"even touching shoulders,"},{"time":643701,"text":"it's no problem."},{"time":645408,"text":"Who fights while they walk?"},{"time":647000,"text":"That's why in negotiations,\noften, when things get tough,"},{"time":650000,"text":"people go for walks in the woods."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652419,"text":"So the idea came to me\nof, what about inspiring a path,"},{"time":657865,"text":"a route -- think the Silk Route,\nthink the Appalachian Trail --"},{"time":661527,"text":"that followed in the footsteps of Abraham?"},{"time":665777,"text":"People said, \"That's crazy. You can't."},{"time":667626,"text":"You can't retrace the footsteps\nof Abraham -- it's too insecure,"},{"time":670662,"text":"you've got to cross all these borders,"},{"time":672544,"text":"it goes across 10 different countries\nin the Middle East,"},{"time":675250,"text":"because it unites them all.\""},{"time":677090,"text":"And so we studied the idea at Harvard."},{"time":678950,"text":"We did our due diligence."},{"time":680204,"text":"And then a few years ago,"},{"time":681427,"text":"a group of us, about 25 of us\nfrom 10 different countries,"},{"time":684181,"text":"decided to see if we could retrace\nthe footsteps of Abraham,"},{"time":687385,"text":"going from his initial birthplace\nin the city of Urfa"},{"time":689909,"text":"in Southern Turkey, Northern Mesopotamia."},{"time":692588,"text":"And we then took a bus and took some walks"},{"time":695572,"text":"and went to Harran, where, in the Bible,\nhe sets off on his journey."},{"time":699753,"text":"Then we crossed the border\ninto Syria, went to Aleppo,"},{"time":702330,"text":"which, turns out, is named after Abraham."},{"time":704702,"text":"We went to Damascus,"},{"time":706000,"text":"which has a long history\nassociated with Abraham."},{"time":708768,"text":"We then came to Northern Jordan,"},{"time":711554,"text":"to Jerusalem -- which is all\nabout Abraham -- to Bethlehem,"},{"time":716604,"text":"and finally, to the place\nwhere he's buried, in Hebron."},{"time":719999,"text":"So effectively, we went from womb to tomb."},{"time":722306,"text":"We showed it could be done."},{"time":723631,"text":"It was an amazing journey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725334,"text":"Let me ask you a question."},{"time":727000,"text":"How many of you have had the experience\nof being in a strange neighborhood"},{"time":731387,"text":"or strange land,"},{"time":733627,"text":"and a total stranger, perfect stranger,"},{"time":736816,"text":"comes up to you\nand shows you some kindness --"},{"time":739562,"text":"maybe invites you into their home,\ngives you a drink,"},{"time":742085,"text":"gives you a coffee, gives you a meal?"},{"time":743888,"text":"How many of you have ever\nhad that experience?"},{"time":746082,"text":"That's the essence of the Abraham Path."},{"time":748897,"text":"That's what you discover as you go\ninto these villages in the Middle East"},{"time":752438,"text":"where you expect hostility,"},{"time":753797,"text":"and you get the most amazing hospitality,"},{"time":756368,"text":"all associated with Abraham:"},{"time":757801,"text":"\"In the name of Father Ibrahim,\nlet me offer you some food.\""},{"time":761585,"text":"So what we discovered"},{"time":762792,"text":"is that Abraham is not just a figure\nout of a book for those people;"},{"time":766024,"text":"he's alive, he's a living presence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769204,"text":"And to make a long story short,"},{"time":771355,"text":"in the last couple of years now,"},{"time":773441,"text":"thousands of people have begun to walk\nparts of the path of Abraham"},{"time":778301,"text":"in the Middle East,"},{"time":779658,"text":"enjoying the hospitality\nof the people there."},{"time":782737,"text":"They've begun to walk\nin Israel and Palestine,"},{"time":786000,"text":"in Jordan, in Turkey, in Syria."},{"time":788744,"text":"It's an amazing experience."},{"time":790077,"text":"Men, women, young people, old people --"},{"time":792386,"text":"more women than men,\nactually, interestingly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":795241,"text":"For those who can't walk,"},{"time":797200,"text":"who are unable to get there right now,"},{"time":799739,"text":"people started to organize walks\nin cities, in their own communities."},{"time":803383,"text":"In Cincinnati, for instance,\nthey organized a walk"},{"time":805781,"text":"from a church to a mosque to a synagogue\nand all had an Abrahamic meal together."},{"time":809647,"text":"It was Abraham Path Day."},{"time":811133,"text":"In São Paulo, Brazil,\nit's become an annual event"},{"time":813563,"text":"for thousands of people to run\nin a virtual Abraham Path Run,"},{"time":817415,"text":"uniting the different communities."},{"time":819210,"text":"The media love it; they really adore it."},{"time":822214,"text":"They lavish attention on it\nbecause it's visual"},{"time":825692,"text":"and it spreads the idea,"},{"time":827380,"text":"this idea of Abrahamic hospitality,\nof kindness towards strangers."},{"time":831786,"text":"And just a couple weeks ago,\nthere was an NPR story on it."},{"time":836589,"text":"Last month,"},{"time":837781,"text":"there was a piece\nin the Manchester Guardian about it,"},{"time":843722,"text":"two whole pages."},{"time":846349,"text":"And they quoted a villager"},{"time":849593,"text":"who said, \"This walk connects\nus to the world.\""},{"time":852704,"text":"He said, \"It was like a light\nthat went on in our lives --"},{"time":855545,"text":"it brought us hope.\""},{"time":857436,"text":"And so that's what it's about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":859542,"text":"But it's not just about psychology;"},{"time":861372,"text":"it's about economics."},{"time":862872,"text":"Because as people walk, they spend money."},{"time":866000,"text":"And this woman right here, Um Ahmad,"},{"time":869000,"text":"is a woman who lives on the path\nin Northern Jordan."},{"time":872174,"text":"She's desperately poor."},{"time":874000,"text":"She's partially blind,\nher husband can't work,"},{"time":877669,"text":"she's got seven kids."},{"time":880113,"text":"But what she can do is cook."},{"time":882671,"text":"And so she's begun to cook\nfor some groups of walkers"},{"time":885236,"text":"who come through the village\nand have a meal in her home."},{"time":888864,"text":"They sit on the floor --\nshe doesn't even have a tablecloth."},{"time":892188,"text":"She makes the most delicious food,"},{"time":894000,"text":"that's fresh from the herbs\nin the surrounding countryside."},{"time":897146,"text":"And so more and more walkers have come,"},{"time":899297,"text":"and lately she's begun to earn an income\nto support her family."},{"time":903215,"text":"And so she told our team there, she said,"},{"time":906116,"text":"\"You have made me visible"},{"time":909306,"text":"in a village where people\nwere once ashamed to look at me.\""},{"time":913755,"text":"That's the potential of the Abraham Path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":916000,"text":"There are literally hundreds\nof those kinds of communities"},{"time":918786,"text":"across the Middle East, across the path."},{"time":922196,"text":"The potential is basically\nto change the game."},{"time":925459,"text":"And to change the game, you have to change\nthe frame, the way we see things --"},{"time":929189,"text":"to change the frame\nfrom hostility to hospitality,"},{"time":934531,"text":"from terrorism to tourism."},{"time":937000,"text":"And in that sense, the Abraham Path"},{"time":939761,"text":"is a game-changer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941887,"text":"Let me just show you one thing."},{"time":943689,"text":"I have a little acorn here"},{"time":945323,"text":"that I picked up while I was walking\non the path earlier this year."},{"time":949366,"text":"Now, the acorn is associated\nwith the oak tree, of course --"},{"time":952237,"text":"grows into an oak tree,\nwhich is associated with Abraham."},{"time":955339,"text":"The path right now is like an acorn;"},{"time":957306,"text":"it's still in its early phase."},{"time":959393,"text":"What would the oak tree look like?"},{"time":961337,"text":"When I think back to my childhood,"},{"time":963000,"text":"a good part of which I spent,\nafter being born here in Chicago,"},{"time":965977,"text":"I spent in Europe."},{"time":967811,"text":"If you had been in the ruins of, say,\nLondon in 1945, or Berlin,"},{"time":974541,"text":"and you had said,"},{"time":975764,"text":"\"Sixty years from now,"},{"time":977471,"text":"this is going to be the most peaceful,\nprosperous part of the planet,\""},{"time":980820,"text":"people would have thought\nyou were certifiably insane."},{"time":984158,"text":"But they did it, thanks\nto a common identity, Europe,"},{"time":988000,"text":"and a common economy."},{"time":990000,"text":"So my question is,\nif it can be done in Europe,"},{"time":993333,"text":"why not in the Middle East?"},{"time":995000,"text":"Why not, thanks to a common identity,\nwhich is the story of Abraham,"},{"time":999711,"text":"and thanks to a common economy that\nwould be based, in good part, on tourism?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005190,"text":"So let me conclude, then,"},{"time":1007421,"text":"by saying that in the last 35 years,"},{"time":1010794,"text":"as I've worked\nin some of the most dangerous,"},{"time":1013235,"text":"difficult and intractable conflicts\naround the planet,"},{"time":1016186,"text":"I have yet to see one conflict\nthat I felt could not be transformed."},{"time":1022338,"text":"It's not easy, of course."},{"time":1024703,"text":"But it's possible."},{"time":1026466,"text":"It was done in South Africa."},{"time":1028430,"text":"It was done in Northern Ireland."},{"time":1030339,"text":"It could be done anywhere."},{"time":1031880,"text":"It simply depends on us."},{"time":1034530,"text":"It depends on us taking the third side."},{"time":1037922,"text":"So let me invite you to consider\ntaking the third side,"},{"time":1041558,"text":"even as a very small step."},{"time":1043248,"text":"We're about to take a break in a moment."},{"time":1045494,"text":"Just go up to someone"},{"time":1047495,"text":"who's from a different culture,\na different country,"},{"time":1050162,"text":"a different ethnicity --\nsome difference --"},{"time":1052541,"text":"and engage them in a conversation."},{"time":1054202,"text":"Listen to them."},{"time":1055460,"text":"That's a third-side act."},{"time":1057000,"text":"That's walking Abraham's Path."},{"time":1059308,"text":"After a TED Talk,"},{"time":1060857,"text":"why not a TED Walk?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1062330,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1063775,"text":"So let me just leave you\nwith three things."},{"time":1067962,"text":"One is, the secret to peace\nis the third side."},{"time":1073386,"text":"The third side is us."},{"time":1075830,"text":"Each of us, with a single step,"},{"time":1079425,"text":"can take the world, can bring the world"},{"time":1082169,"text":"a step closer to peace."},{"time":1085318,"text":"There's an old African proverb that goes:"},{"time":1087398,"text":"\"When spiderwebs unite,"},{"time":1089588,"text":"they can halt even the lion.\""},{"time":1092670,"text":"If we're able to unite\nour third-side webs of peace,"},{"time":1096969,"text":"we can even halt the lion of war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1100001,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1101176,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}